## Entry quality (apply to every entry)

**Self-describing first sentence.** The opening sentence should work as a standalone summary — `sdd status` truncates descriptions, so a reader seeing the opening alone should understand what the entry is about. Calibration:

- `medium` — The opening is purely reference-dependent (e.g. "Plan for d-tac-X" or "Closes s-prc-Y") and the body doesn't carry the substance either. Worth naming; easy to correct post-capture.
- `low` — The opening leans on a reference but the body makes the substance clear. Editorial suggestion.
- No finding — Referencing related entries is standard practice (e.g. "Implemented X per d-tac-Y plan" for closing actions). Body conveys substance.

Prose is mechanical-fix territory per the immutability calibration; never flag opening style as `high`.
